  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Lucia Weston says that an article entitled &quot;Right and Wrong&quot; is finished. Lucia went to an anti-slavery meeting and comments on Anne Warren Weston and the Ammidon sisters. She gives news of the family. She called on Mrs. Todd. She speaks of a &quot;battle being fought at Lowell&quot; between the old and new organizations. She mentions a plan to have a bust of William Lloyd Garrison done by Shobal Vail Clevenger. Lucia expects to sell plaster casts of the bust at the next anti-slavery fair. John A. Collins is looking for a house in Boston.</subfield>
